title: For Sale/Trade:  Kel-Tec Sub2000, .40 caliber, six Glock magazines, good condition.
postcontent:
I have for sale a Kel-Tec Sub2000 chambered in .40 caliber as well as three ten-round and three fifteen-round Glock magazines, the box and manual, and the small keychain used to lock the rifle when it is in its folded position.
The rifle has seen light range use, as well as the magazines, and has functioned at 99% in the three years I've owned it. I've only experienced stove-piping over several rounds of reloaded frangible ammunition and never had any problems with UMC, Winchester, or any other makers of note. The trigger is crisp and firm, the action is smooth and consistent, and this little thing is a tack driver inside of 75 yards. I mean TIGHT. 
This little baby folds in half to become 18" long by 6" tall at the grip and locks for security if for instance you were to take it camping and needed to step away. 
It is infinitely customizable with at least three manufacturers making inexpensive fore-end kits allowing for optics, handles, lights, etc. and extremely versatile as it is built hardily out of reinforced polymer and hardened steel, and chambers the venerable .40 S&W pistol cartridge.
The Kel-Tec Sub2000 is the perfect sub-rifle for self defense, as it is extremely manageable and very consistent, but would be equally comfortable, and very useful, as a varmint rifle. According to 2013 TN Hunting Regulations, responsible hunters may utilize .40 caliber ammunition to hunt deer!
These rifles are going for 400 plus tax without the boon of extra, high-quality magazines. Maybe you can find a better deal, but this rifle is a tried and true piece of equipment.

Someone could be doing it right now, and first person to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just before you, I will notify you within a short time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you shortly.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK WHETHER THE GUN IS STILL AVAILABLE! I WILL NOT RESPOND.

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Are there any other fees, in addition to the price and taxes? NICS, background check, etc?
A. No.

Q. What is the tax rate?
A. 9.5%

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to offer them to me at well below wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military as well as highly accurate, competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Q. Is the price firm? Will you take XXX (70% of the asking price)?
A. The price is firm.

Q. Can you help me mount a scope/replace a trigger/fix a feeding problem?
A. Sorry, I do not do gunsmithing.

Q. Will you ship?
A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area. Shipping via FedEx will be $25.
